\begin_layout Subsection
Radiative-Convective Equilibrium (RCE)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A two-dimensional, dry radiative convective equilibrium test case is devised
 to mimic some properties of atmospheric convection, in particular the difficult
y resolving the flow at coarse resolution.
 The domain is 160km wide, 10km tall and is resolved by 640 cells in the
 horizontal and 40 in the vertical (
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x=\Delta z=250$
\end_inset

m).
 The top and bottom boundaries are zero mass flux and the lateral boundaries
 are periodic.
 A heat flux of 
\begin_inset Formula $h=10^{-3}\text{m}^{2}\text{s}^{-3}$
\end_inset

 is imposed at the bottom boundary leading to a boundary condition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial b/\partial z=-h/\alpha\text{s}^{-2}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=100\ \text{m}^{2}\text{s}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 is the buoyancy diffusivity.
 The top boundary has 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial b/\partial z=0$
\end_inset

.
 Diffusion is applied to the momentum equation with a coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu=70.7\ \text{m}^{2}\text{s}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 so as to give a Plank constant of 
\begin_inset Formula $0.707$
\end_inset

.
 Uniform cooling of 
\begin_inset Formula $-1\times10^{-7}\text{m}\text{s}^{-3}$
\end_inset

 is applied to the domain to maintain equilibrium.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The fluid is initially stationary with 
\begin_inset Formula $b=0$
\end_inset

.
 In order to quickly and reproducibly initialise instability, 
\begin_inset Formula $b=10^{-4}\text{m}^{2}\text{s}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 is imposed in a square of side length 2000m at the centre in the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 direction and at the ground.
 The simulation is run using a time step of 
\begin_inset Formula $5\ \text{s}$
\end_inset

.
 A quasi-steady, choatic state is reached after about 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{5}\text{s}$
\end_inset

 and the simulation is run for a further 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{5}\text{s}$
\end_inset

 to calculate time averages.
 
\end_layout

